         <p>Songs from a Free Space*
			</p>
         <p>Alone
				Deborah Hiller
			</p>
         <p>She who walks alone and dreams
				will remain lonely.
				She who sleeps with her pillow
				only dreams of her pillow as partner.
				But she who sits in her cell,
				and writes
				will master this world.
			</p>
         <p>*From <hi rend="italic:true; fontSize:0.0; kerning:0;">Songs from a Free Space/Writings by Women in</hi>
            <hi rend="italic:true; fontSize:0.0; kerning:0;">Prison</hi>, edited by Carol Muske and Gail Rosenblum, New
				York, n. d.
			</p>
